history.content:
Incoming intended LSCS freshman, planning to take CS 61A and EECS 16A in fall semester. Got a 5 on AP Calc BC and took a 1-semester Hon Diff Eq course ("UC approved" whatever that means??), but I hear that EECS 16A uses lin alg, which I don't have experience in... Is my math skill good enough for 16A?

Side note, got a 5 on AP CS A but ik it's super easy compared to 61A. Planning to work through the first few chapters on the online textbook (https://composingprograms.com/pages/11-getting-started.html). Any other tips on how to prepare myself for 61A?
